sql:
SELECT COUNT(metric_id) AS total_metrics
FROM engagement_metrics
WHERE program_id = (SELECT program_id FROM community_programs WHERE program_name = 'Example Program');

SELECT COUNT(program_id) AS active_programs
FROM community_programs
WHERE end_date > CURRENT_DATE;

SELECT program_name, description, end_date
FROM community_programs
WHERE end_date < '2022-01-01';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT program_id) AS total_unique_programs
FROM engagement_metrics
WHERE date >= DATE('now', '-30 days');

external_knowledge:
- "Blooming" here metaphorically refers to the start of programs within a specific timeframe;
- "Garden of 2022" represents the calendar year 2022 during which the programs began;
- "Average participants" refers to the average metric value recorded for each program, which can be seen as the 'fragrance' they carry.

